  "explanation": {
    "what_is_bias": "In a linear map y = Wx + b, the vector b is the bias. It shifts the activation so a neuron need not rely only on zero-mean inputs. In this student, Conv2d layers use bias=False; affine offsets appear as BatchNorm \u03b2 (.bn.bias) and the final Linear classifier .fc.bias.",
    "why_separate_file": "Deployment and audit often pack convolutions (weights) separately from BN scale/shift and classifier bias. The full .pt is still required for training resume and exact PyTorch eval; the bias file is an export aid."
